  "prompt": "How 2016 demonetization is different from that of 1970s?",
  "response": "The demonetization in 2016 and the one in the 1970s have several key differences:\n\n2016 Demonetization:\n1. Sudden announcement by PM Modi\n2. Targeted specific high-denomination notes (\u20b9500 and \u20b91000)\n3. Objective: Combat black money, terror financing, counterfeit currency\n4. Digital transaction promotion\n5. More comprehensive banking infrastructure\n6. Higher technological preparedness\n7. Broader economic impact\n8. Implemented during digital era\n9. Immediate nationwide implementation\n10. Greater public scrutiny and media coverage\n\n1970s Demonetization:\n1. Implemented by Morarji Desai\n2. Less sudden and more gradual process\n3. Primary objective was to control black money\n4. Limited technological infrastructure\n5. Less developed banking system\n6. Primarily cash-based economy\n7. Limited digital transaction options\n8. Relatively smaller economic impact\n9. Less transparent implementation\n10. Limited public communication\n\nKey Distinctions:\n- Scale of implementation\n- Technological context\n- Economic preparedness\n- Broader strategic objectives\n- Public awareness and communication\n\nBoth demonetization efforts shared the fundamental goal of reducing black money, but the 2016 version was more comprehensive and technologically advanced.",
